## The Velora Bella Bridal Experience: What to Expect

We believe the journey to your wedding day look should feel just as luxurious as the look itself. Here's how we take care of our brides from the very first message to the last touch-up.

### Step 1: Your Consultation

Everything begins with a conversation. We want to know:

- **Your vision** — romantic and soft? Bold and dramatic? Timeless and classic?
- **Your dress and accessories** — so we can ensure everything is cohesive
- **Your skin** — concerns, sensitivities, and current routine
- **Your venue and timing** — so we can plan your look for the lighting and longevity you need

This isn't a quick 10-minute call. We take our time, because *you deserve that.*

### Step 2: Your Bridal Trial

Your trial is non-negotiable. It is, without question, one of the most important appointments on your wedding planning calendar.

At your trial, we:

✔ Test your full makeup look from start to finish
✔ Photograph you in natural light to see how your look translates on camera
✔ Make any adjustments to color, intensity, or finish
✔ Time the application so your wedding day schedule is seamless
✔ Address any skin concerns before the big day

**Pro tip from our team:** Schedule your trial 4–6 weeks before your wedding. Close enough that your skin is in its pre-wedding routine, but early enough that we have time to refine anything.

### Step 3: Your Wedding Day

On your wedding morning, we arrive **prepared, professional, and ready to make magic.**

Our brides consistently tell us the same thing afterward: *"I felt so calm because I trusted you completely."*

That's exactly what we aim for. Your job on your wedding morning is to breathe, sip your coffee, and soak in every single moment. Our job is to handle everything else.

